ate Role with `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` for secrets\n31:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n32:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"secrets\"`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T1.4**: Create Router RoleBinding to bind ServiceAccount to Role\n35:   - Purpose: Establish SA → Role binding within namespace\n36:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n37:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: RoleBinding\"`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T1.5**: Implement Router Role namespace isolation\n40:   - Purpose: Ensure Role and RoleBinding are namespace-scoped (not cluster-wide)\n41:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n42:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep \"namespace: agentcube\"`\n43: \n44: ### Phase 2: WorkloadManager RBAC (ST-2)\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create WorkloadManager ServiceAccount template\n47:   - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount for WorkloadManager (cluster-scoped identity)\n48:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n49:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ServiceAccount\" | grep \"name: workloadmanager\"`\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.2**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for agents.x-k8s.io CRDs\n52:   - Purpose: Grant permissions for `sandboxes` (full CRUD)\n53:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n54:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A15 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"sandboxes\"`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **T2.3**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io CRDs\n57:   - Purpose: Grant permissions for `sandboxclaims`, `sandboxtemplates`, `sandboxwarmpools` and status subresource\n58:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n59:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A15 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"sandboxclaims\"`\n60: \n61: - [ ] **T2.4**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh CRDs\n62:   - Purpose: Grant full CRUD for `codeinterpreters` + status/finalizers, read-only for `agentruntimes` + status updates\n63:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n64:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A20 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"codeinterpreters\"`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T2.5**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for core Kubernetes resources\n67:   - Purpose: Grant read-only for `pods`, full CRUD for `secrets`\n68:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n69:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A25 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"pods\"`\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.6**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for TokenReview\n72:   - Purpose: Grant `create` permission for `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews`\n73:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n74:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A30 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"tokenreviews\"`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T2.7**: Create WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n77:   - Purpose: Bind ClusterRole to ServiceAccount (cluster-wide binding)\n78:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n79:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A10 \"kind: ClusterRoleBinding\"`\n80: \n81: ### Phase 3: Deployment Integration (ST-3)\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.1**: Integrate Router ServiceAccount into Router Deployment\n84:   - Purpose: Set `serviceAccountName` in Router Deployment spec when `router.serviceAccountName` is provided\n85:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n86:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"serviceAccountName: test-sa\"`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.2**: Integrate WorkloadManager ServiceAccount into WorkloadManager Deployment\n89:   - Purpose: Set fixed `serviceAccountName: workloadmanager` in WorkloadManager Deployment\n90:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n91:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"name: workloadmanager\" | grep \"serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\"`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T3.3**: Update values.yaml with router.rbac.create configuration\n94:   - Purpose: Add `router.rbac.create: false` default and `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` default\n95:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n96:   - Verification: `grep \"rbac:\" manifests/charts/base/values.yaml && grep \"create: false\" manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n97: \n98: ### Phase 4: Permission Validation (ST-4)\n99: \n100: - [ ] **T4.1**: Verify Router Role has no wildcard permissions\n101:   - Purpose: Ensure no `*` in resources or verbs (least-privilege compliance)\n102:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n103:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'resources:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"`\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T4.2**: Verify Router Role has no TokenReview permission\n106:   - Purpose: Router should only have secrets access (no authentication API)\n107:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n108:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A5 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"tokenreviews\" || echo \"OK\"`\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T4.3**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has no Pod create/delete permissions\n111:   - Purpose: WorkloadManager creates pods via Sandbox CRD, not directly\n112:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n113:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"pods\" | grep -E \"(create|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.4**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has no AgentRuntime delete permission\n116:   - Purpose: WorkloadManager only reads AgentRuntimes, cannot delete\n117:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n118:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"agentruntimes\" | grep \"delete\" || echo \"OK\"`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.5**: Verify all ClusterRole rules use correct API groups\n121:   - Purpose: Validate API groups: `agents.x-k8s.io`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io`, `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, `authentication.k8s.io`, core `\"\"`\n122:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n123:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A50 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"apiGroups\"`\n124: \n125: ### Phase 5: Helm Chart Validation Tests (ST-5)\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T5.1**: Run Helm lint on chart with RBAC enabled\n128:   - Purpose: Validate chart syntax with Router RBAC enabled\n129:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n130:   - Verification: `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa`\n131: \n132: - [ ] **T5.2**: Test Router RBAC disabled scenario\n133:   - Purpose: Verify no Router RBAC resources rendered when `router.rbac.create=false`\n134:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n135:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=false | grep \"kind: Role\" || echo \"OK\"`\n136: \n137: - [ ] **T5.3**: Test Router RBAC validation guard failure\n138:   - Purpose: Verify template fails when `router.rbac.create=true` without serviceAccountName\n139:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n140:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T5.4**: Test Router RBAC rendering with custom namespace\n143:   - Purpose: Verify RBAC resources use correct namespace from Helm release\n144:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n145:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep \"namespace: agentcube\"`\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T5.5**: Test WorkloadManager RBAC always rendered\n148:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager RBAC renders regardless of Router RBAC setting\n149:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n150:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=false | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\"`\n151: \n152: ### Phase 6: Kubernetes API Validation Tests (ST-6)\n153: \n154: - [ ] **T6.1**: Validate Router RBAC resources with kubectl dry-run\n155:   - Purpose: Verify Router RBAC YAML is valid Kubernetes schema\n156:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n157:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa > /tmp/router-rbac.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/router-rbac.yaml | grep \"serviceaccount\"`\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T6.2**: Validate WorkloadManager RBAC resources with kubectl dry-run\n160:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager RBAC YAML is valid Kubernetes schema\n161:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n162:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" > /tmp/workloadmanager-rbac.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/workloadmanager-rbac.yaml | grep \"clusterrole\"`\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T6.3**: Validate complete chart with kubectl dry-run\n165:   - Purpose: Verify entire rendered chart is valid for Kubernetes API\n166:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n167:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa > /tmp/rendered.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml`\n168: \n169: ### Phase 7: Permission Matrix Tests (ST-7)\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T7.1**: Test Router ServiceAccount can access secrets in own namespace\n172:   - Purpose: Verify `kubectl auth can-i` returns `yes` for Router SA secrets access\n173:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n174:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i get secrets --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube` (expected: yes)\n175: \n176: - [ ] **T7.2**: Test Router ServiceAccount cannot access secrets in other namespace\n177:   - Purpose: Verify namespace isolation - Router SA forbidden in other namespaces\n178:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n179:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i get secrets -n other-ns --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router` (expected: no)\n180: \n181: - [ ] **T7.3**: Test Router ServiceAccount cannot create pods\n182:   - Purpose: Verify Router has no pod creation permission\n183:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n184:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube` (expected: no)\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T7.4**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create sandboxes\n187:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager has sandbox creation permission\n188:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n189:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T7.5**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create codeinterpreters\n192:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager has CodeInterpreter CRD permissions\n193:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n194:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T7.6**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount cannot create pods directly\n197:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager cannot create Pods (only via Sandbox CRD)\n198:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n199:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: no)\n200: \n201: - [ ] **T7.7**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create TokenReviews\n202:   - Purpose: Verify TokenReview create permission for authentication\n203:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n204:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create tokenreviews.authentication.k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n205: \n206: - [ ] **T7.8**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount cannot delete AgentRuntimes\n207:   - Purpose: Verify AgentRuntime is read-only for WorkloadManager\n208:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n209:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i delete agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: no)\n210: \n211: ### Phase 8: Security Audit Tests (ST-8)\n212: \n213: - [ ] **T8.1**: Verify no ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding for Router\n214:   - Purpose: Router should only have namespace-scoped Role (not cluster-wide)\n215:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n216:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\" || echo \"OK\"`\n217: \n218: - [ ] **T8.2**: Verify Router Role metadata includes namespace\n219:   - Purpose: Confirm Role is namespace-scoped (not cluster-scoped)\n220:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n221:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep -A3 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"namespace\"`\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T8.3**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has least-privilege verbs for pods\n224:   - Purpose: Pods should only have `get,list,watch` (no create/update/delete)\n225:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n226:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A8 \"pods\" | grep -E \"(create|update|patch|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T8.4**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has least-privilege verbs for agentruntimes\n229:   - Purpose: AgentRuntimes should only have `get,list,watch` (no create/delete)\n230:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n231:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A8 \"agentruntimes\" | grep \"verbs\" | grep -E \"(create|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n232: \n233: - [ ] **T8.5**: Verify no wildcard `*` permissions in any RBAC rule\n234:   - Purpose: Security audit - wildcards violate least-privilege principle\n235:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/`\n236:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"`\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Task Dependencies\n241: \n242: ```\n243: Phase 1 (Router RBAC Foundation) ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n244: T1.1 (SA) ──┬── T1.2 (validation guard)\n245:             ├── T1.3 (Role)\n246:             ├── T1.4 (RoleBinding)\n247:             └── T1.5 (namespace isolation)\n248: \n249: Phase 2 (WorkloadManager RBAC) ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n250: T2.1 (SA) ──┬── T2.2 (agents.x-k8s.io)\n251:             ├── T2.3 (extensions.agents.x-k8s.io)\n252:             ├── T2.4 (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh)\n253:             ├── T2.5 (core resources)\n254:             ├── T2.6 (TokenReview)\n255:             └── T2.7 (ClusterRoleBinding)\n256: \n257: Phase 3 (Deployment Integration) ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n258: T1.1-T1.5 ──┬── T3.1 (Router Deployment)\n259: T2.1-T2.7 ──┬── T3.2 (WorkloadManager Deployment)\n260:             └── T3.3 (values.yaml)\n261: \n262: Phase 4 (Permission Validation) ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n263: T1.1-T3.3 ──┬── T4.1-T4.5 (permission matrix validation)\n264: \n265: Phase 5 (Helm Validation) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n266: T1.1-T4.5 ──┬── T5.1-T5.5 (Helm template tests)\n267: \n268: Phase 6 (Kubernetes API Validation) ──────────────────────────────────────────\n269: T5.1-T5.5 ──┬── T6.1-T6.3 (kubectl dry-run tests)\n270: \n271: Phase 7 (Permission Matrix Tests) ────────────────────────────────────────────\n272: T6.1-T6.3 ──┬── T7.1-T7.8 (kubectl auth can-i tests) [requires cluster]\n273: \n274: Phase 8 (Security Audit) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n275: T1.1-T7.8 ──┬── T8.1-T8.5 (security audit checks)\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ## Verification Commands\n281: \n282: | Task Phase | Verification Command |\n283: |------------|----------------------|\n284: | Phase 1 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: ServiceAccount\" \\| grep \"name: test-sa\"` |\n285: | Phase 2 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A50 \"kind: ClusterRole\" \\| grep \"sandboxes\"` |\n286: | Phase 3 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"serviceAccountName: test-sa\"` |\n287: | Phase 4 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"` |\n288: | Phase 5 | `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa` |\n289: | Phase 6 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" > /tmp/rendered.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml` |\n290: | Phase 7 | `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (requires cluster deployment) |\n291: | Phase 8 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\" \\| grep -v workloadmanager || echo \"OK\"` |\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## Acceptance Criteria\n296: \n297: - [ ] Router ServiceAccount rendered when `router.rbac.create=true`\n298: - [ ] Router Role has namespace-scoped secrets permissions (get/list/watch/create/update/patch/delete)\n299: - [ ] Router RoleBinding binds Router SA to Router Role within namespace\n300: - [ ] Router RBAC validation guard: fail if `router.rbac.create=true` without `router.serviceAccountName`\n301: - [ ] Router RBAC not rendered when `router.rbac.create=false`\n302: - [ ] Router RBAC has no cluster-scoped resources (no ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding)\n303: - [ ] Router RBAC uses correct namespace from `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n304: - [ ] WorkloadManager ServiceAccount always rendered\n305: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes (full CRUD)\n306: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io (sandboxclaims, sandboxtemplates, sandboxwarmpools + status)\n307: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters (full CRUD + status/finalizers)\n308: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes (read-only + status updates)\n309: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for core pods (read-only: get/list/watch)\n310: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for core secrets (full CRUD)\n311: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permission for authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews (create only)\n312: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding binds WM SA to WM ClusterRole\n313: - [ ] Router Deployment uses `router.serviceAccountName` when provided\n314: - [ ] WorkloadManager Deployment uses fixed `serviceAccountName: workloadmanager`\n315: - [ ] values.yaml includes `router.rbac.create: false` default\n316: - [ ] values.yaml includes `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` default\n317: - [ ] Helm lint passes with 0 errors\n318: - [ ] Rendered YAML validates with kubectl dry-run\n319: - [ ] Router SA can access secrets in own namespace (kubectl auth can-i)\n320: - [ ] Router SA cannot access secrets in other namespaces (namespace isolation)\n321: - [ ] Router SA cannot create pods (least-privilege)\n322: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create sandboxes CRDs\n323: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create codeinterpreter CRDs\n324: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA cannot create pods directly (only via Sandbox)\n325: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA cannot delete agentruntimes (read-only)\n326: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create TokenReviews\n327: - [ ] No wildcard `*` permissions in any RBAC rule\n328: - [ ] Router Role has no TokenReview permission\n329: - [ ] All RBAC rules use correct API groups\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## File Changes Summary\n334: \n335: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n336: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n337: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Create | 49 | Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding - conditional rendering) |\n338: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Create | 131 | WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) |\n339: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Modify | 81 | Add serviceAccountName field integration |\n340: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | Modify | - | Add serviceAccountName: workloadmanager (if missing) |\n341: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Modify | 57 | Add router.rbac.create and router.serviceAccountName defaults |\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ## Implementation Notes\n346: \n347: ### Router RBAC Conditional Rendering Pattern\n348: \n349: ```yaml\n350: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n351: {{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n352: {{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n353: {{- end }}\n354: apiVersion: v1\n355: kind: ServiceAccount\n356: metadata:\n357:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n358:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n359:   labels:\n360:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n361: ---\n362: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n363: kind: Role\n364: metadata:\n365:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n366:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n367:   labels:\n368:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n369: rules:\n370:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n371:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n372:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n373: ---\n374: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n375: kind: RoleBinding\n376: metadata:\n377:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n378:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n379:   labels:\n380:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n381: roleRef:\n382:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n383:   kind: Role\n384:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n385: subjects:\n386:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n387:     name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n388:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n389: {{- end }}\n390: ```\n391: \n392: ### WorkloadManager ClusterRole Permission Matrix\n393: \n394: ```yaml\n395: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n396: kind: ClusterRole\n397: metadata:\n398:   name: workloadmanager\n399: rules:\n400:   - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n401:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n402:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n403:   \n404:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n405:     resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n406:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n407:   \n408:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n409:     resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n410:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n411:   \n412:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n413:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n414:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n415:   \n416:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n417:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\", \"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n418:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n419:   \n420:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n421:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n422:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n423:   \n424:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n425:     resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n426:     verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n427:   \n428:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n429:     resources: [\"pods\"]\n430:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n431:   \n432:   - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n433:     resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n434:     verbs: [\"create\"]\n435:   \n436:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n437:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n438:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ### RBAC Scope Design Rationale\n442: \n443: | Component | Scope | Reason |\n444: |-----------|-------|--------|\n445: | Router | Namespace-scoped (Role/RoleBinding) | Router only manages secrets in its namespace (JWT signing keys, identity secrets). No cluster-wide access needed. |\n446: | WorkloadManager | Cluster-scoped (ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding) | Agent-sandbox CRDs are cluster-scoped; WorkloadManager manages sandboxes across namespaces. Cross-namespace sandbox lifecycle management requires cluster-wide permissions. |\n447: \n448: ### Least Privilege Principles\n449: \n450: | Resource | Verbs | Reason |\n451: |----------|-------|--------|\n452: | pods | get, list, watch | Read-only monitoring; WorkloadManager creates pods via Sandbox CRD, not directly |\n453: | agentruntimes | get, list, watch | Read-only reference; WorkloadManager references AgentRuntimes but does not manage lifecycle |\n454: | agentruntimes/status | update, patch | Status updates only; no delete permission |\n455: | sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch | Status subresource pattern; separate from main resource CRUD |\n456: | codeinterpreters/finalizers | update | Finalizer management only; limited to finalizer operations |\n457: | tokenreviews | create | One-shot authentication; no read/delete (ephemeral operation) |\n458: \n459: ---\n460: \n461: ## Implementation Timeline\n462: \n463: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n464: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n465: | Phase 1: Router RBAC Foundation | T1.1-T1.5 | Completed | 100% |\n466: | Phase 2: WorkloadManager RBAC | T2.1-T2.7 | Completed | 100% |\n467: | Phase 3: Deployment Integration | T3.1-T3.3 | Completed | 100% |\n468: | Phase 4: Permission Validation | T4.1-T4.5 | Pending | 0% |\n469: | Phase 5: Helm Validation | T5.1-T5.5 | Pending | 0% |\n470: | Phase 6: Kubernetes API Validation | T6.1-T6.3 | Pending | 0% |\n471: | Phase 7: Permission Matrix Tests | T7.1-T7.8 | Pending | 0% |\n472: | Phase 8: Security Audit | T8.1-T8.5 | Pending | 0% |\n473: \n474: **Total Progress: 30% Complete (15/50 tasks)**\n475: \n476: ---\n477: \n478: ## References\n479: \n480: - Design: `changes/AR-031/design.md`\n481: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md`\n482: - Proposal: `changes/AR-031/proposal.md`\n483: - AR-030 Helm Chart Design: `changes/AR-030/design.md` (RBAC template patterns)\n484: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n485: - Kubernetes API Reference: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n486: - Helm Template Functions: https://helm.sh/docs/chart_template_guide/function_list/\n487: - agent-sandbox CRDs: https://sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox\n\n(End of file - total 487 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Router RBAC Foundation (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create Router ServiceAccount template with conditional rendering\n  - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount when `router.rbac.create=true`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775885845334,"end":1775885845363}}}}
